> **★★★ COMPACT-ON-BUSTED-CACHE ECONOMICS — BUILT + MEASURED ON THE WIRE
> (2026-06-07). Answers item-7's open cold-wakeup question with real numbers.
> Backstory: a PreUserPrompt hook (human built it in another session) detects an
> evicted prompt-cache and suggests `/compact` before the user re-writes the cold
> context. But /compact ITSELF costs an API call + discards the cache it writes —
> so when is it worth it? Harness: `proxy-experiments/compact_economics.py`
> (self-contained; imports readers from experiments.py). Captures: `logs_compact/`.**
> MECHANISM (all confirmed): `/compact` is NOT a text-`-p` command — it must go via
> `--input-format stream-json --output-format stream-json`, sending one line
> `{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"/compact"}}`. It emits a
> `system/compact_boundary` event (`trigger:manual`, `pre_tokens`, `post_tokens`)
> and PERSISTS to the session; `--resume`/`--fork-session` after it continue from
> the SUMMARY. Control auto-compaction with `CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE=100`
> (never fires) — there is no explicit disable flag. Fork the busted base TWICE
> (`--resume BASE --fork-session`) to get two independent arms from the identical
> cache-busted state. Ran VANILLA proxy (all default-on transforms OFF:
> RELOCATE_*/SORT_TOOLS/STRIP/CANARY=0) so this is NATIVE CLI economics.
> SETUP: sonnet, FORCE_PROMPT_CACHING_5M=1, built a base to **69,370 tok** over 4
> Read+explain turns on a 140KB scratch repo, idled **390s** (busts the 5m cache),
> then Arm A=`/compact`→10 ops vs Arm B=same 10 ops (no compact). Ops = short
> reasoning Qs answerable from context (no re-reads), identical both arms.
> **RESULTS (n=1, on the wire):**
>  · **Compaction ratio:** 69,370 → **2,523 tok** summary (−96.4%).
>  · **Cost of /compact on a busted cache = 91,120 billed tok / $0.369 (sonnet).**
>    Breakdown: it COLD-WROTE **cw5m=87,135** (full history+tools at the 5m write
>    premium) + emitted a **2,524-tok summary OUTPUT** + in=1,461. **That entire
>    87k cache write is DISCARDED** — the next op read=0 from it (the compacted
>    prefix diverges right after tools; even tools weren't reused). So "discarded
>    caching" is real and quantified: ~87k written, ~0 reused.
