>     Region A `gap≤5m` (both warm; reads equal → 5m wins on cheaper write) ·
>     Region B `5–60m` (only 1h stays warm → 1h saves the rewrite) · Region C
>     `>60m` (both evict → 5m cheaper, or don't cache). EXACT: **1h cheaper iff
>     `1.15·n_B − 0.75·n_C > 0.75`** (n_B/n_C = #gaps in B/C). +1.15 per B-gap
>     rescued, −0.75 per C-gap (wasted premium), 0.75 = cold-write premium to clear.
