       earlier uncontrolled "haiku 2/4" does NOT reproduce; with adaptive thinking +
       @-inlined + this phrasing, haiku emits a future-tense preamble ("I'll add…")
       then a bare Edit, and only says "Done. Added…" on the wrap-up turn — the
       sentinel is deferred every time. Generic/conditional phrasing: haiku 0/5 too.
     - `SHORTCIRCUIT_TOOLPATCH` (append protocol to the Edit tool's DESCRIPTION
       in tools[]): **DE-CONFOUNDED via a CONTROLLED A/B (2026-06-03): sonnet
       toolpatch 0/3 vs instruct 3/3 — the tool description is NOT a viable home;
